Folk Song best played on acoustic guitar standard tuning no capo required.
Gaelic traditional Runrig song from 1979,best played on acoustic guitar,from the album highland collection.
Tabbed from 1997 the last time Donnie Munro sang live with Runrig as lead singer,Play with acoustic picking guitar ,or clean electric rhythm again picking strings.

Played with electric guitar with tremolo,slap back and chorus effects,a little fuzz can be added for "hearthammer" refrain,alternatively use the strum guide for a "folk" feel.

Acoustic Guitar Simple guitar pluck to suit,or use strum pattern above to suit,a simple ,reflective optimistic tune.
